<p>Wine grapes grow almost exclusively between thirty and fifty degrees north or south of the <a href="/wiki/Equator" title="Equator">equator</a>. The world's southernmost vineyards are in the <a href="/wiki/Central_Otago" title="Central Otago">Central Otago</a> region of New Zealand's <a href="/wiki/South_Island" title="South Island">South Island</a> near the 45th parallel,<sup id="cite_ref-43" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-43" title=""><span>[</span>44<span>]</span></a></sup> and the northernmost are in <a href="/wiki/Flen" title="Flen">Flen</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sweden" title="Sweden">Sweden</a>, just north of the 59th parallel.<sup id="cite_ref-44" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-44" title=""><span>[</span>45<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
